

Jean-Louis Sagot-Duvauroux published the important book [[Pour la Gratuite]], which interprets free public good as an important indicator of the civilizational process. Free Beer refers to the famous quote by Richard Stallman, saying free software is free, not as in free beer, but as in free speech. However, this French-language profile and interview argues that free beer is just as important.

